    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-06T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-06T04:00:00-05:00" n="347"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Matthews Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> Notes</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d347fn1">Transcribed for this volume from longhand notes in
                        pencil.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Leningrad</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-chapter-heading" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1945-02-06T12:00:00+03:00">February 6, 1945, noon</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">1. Communiqué<note n="2" xml:id="d347fn2">For citations to
                        pertinent documents, see the preceding <persName corresp="#p_PEJ1"
                            >Page</persName> minutes of this meeting.</note>—S.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d347fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName>. (Throughout the
                            <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> notes the editors have
                        added footnote explanations of the more unusual contractions and
                        abbreviations.)</note> thinks wise to issue one</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mol</hi>. Preliminary One suggestion: add <hi
                        rend="underline">“common”</hi> enemy. Likes communiqué. No objection to
                    mention Black Sea area. Must be approved by <persName corresp="#p_S16"
                        >Stalin</persName>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">2. S. announces 3 questions before the 3 F. M. On first
                    point.</p>
                <p>Adding “dismemberment” to Art 12<note n="4" xml:id="d347fn4">Of the draft
                        instrument entitled “Unconditional Surrender of Germany”.</note> &amp; refer
                    to <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss>.</p>
                <pb facs="0754" n="658" xml:id="pg_658"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mol</hi>. Accepts addition of word.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_EA1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eden</hi>
                    </persName>. Another formula “and measures for the dissolution of the German
                    unitary state” Would cover abolition of centralization of Germ. govt.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mol</hi>: Will exercise sup.<note n="5" xml:id="d347fn5"
                        >supreme.</note> power . . .<note n="6" xml:id="d347fn6">Points appear in
                        the original.</note> take measures for dismemberment of G. For peace &amp;
                    security of Europe necessary to dismember G.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>Agreed to add: “And the dismemberment” after demilitarization.</p>
                    <p>No agreement on Russian change.</p>
                </quote>
            </div>
